{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775845214315,"sessionID":"ses_287621e35ffeBybyIcGCUlmjbj","part":{"id":"prt_d789f87fd001W6GW8nx6UgcDWB","messageID":"msg_d789e39a0001GpGwNUx2A3Fide","sessionID":"ses_287621e35ffeBybyIcGCUlmjbj","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_tool-9ede98471a6c470ba8e65d3d44d60390","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"content":"# AR-006 — Sandbox 删除与生命周期管理 Implementation Tasks\n\n**Module**: `pkg/workloadmanager`\n**Language**: Go\n**Size**: M\n**Design Stage**: ST-3 Completed\n\n## Task Breakdown\n\n### Task 1: Create package structure and initialize constants\n- [ ] Verify `pkg/workloadmanager` directory exists\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/defaults.go` (if not exists) - Define timeout and configuration constants\n  - [ ] Define `DefaultSandboxTTL = 8 * time.Hour`\n  - [ ] Define `DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute`\n  - [ ] Define `GCInterval = 15 * time.Second`\n  - [ ] Define `GCSingleTickTimeout = 2 * time.Minute`\n  - [ ] Define `DeleteTimeout = 30 * time.Second`\n  - [ ] Define label constants:\n    - [ ] `SessionIDLabelKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/session-id\"`\n    - [ ] `WorkloadNameLabelKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/workload-name\"`\n    - [ ] `SandboxNameLabelKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/sandbox-name\"`\n    - [ ] `ManagedByLabel = \"managed-by\"`\n    - [ ] `ManagedByValue = \"agentcube-workload-manager\"`\n  - [ ] Define annotation constants:\n    - [ ] `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"`\n    - [ ] `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"`\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/types/sandbox_types.go` (if not exists) - Define sandbox lifecycle types\n  - [ ] Define `SandboxCleanupReason` type\n  - [ ] Define constants: `CleanupReasonManual`, `CleanupReasonIdleTimeout`, `CleanupReasonExpired`\n  - [ ] Define `CleanupAuditEntry` struct\n    - [ ] SessionID, SandboxID, Namespace, Reason, DeletedAt, Success, ErrorMessage\n- [ ] Define GVR constants for Sandbox resources\n  - [ ] `SandboxGVR` for agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/Sandbox\n  - [ ] `SandboxClaimGVR` for extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1/SandboxClaim\n- [ ] Verify package compiles: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n\n**Verification**: Run `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...` to ensure the package structure and constants compile\n\n---\n\n### Task 2: Implement Store interface extensions for lifecycle management\n- [ ] Extend `pkg/store/store.go` Store interface (if not already extended)\n  - [ ] Implement `StoreSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n  - [ ] Implement `GetSandbox(ctx, sessionID string) (*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - [ ] Implement `UpdateSandbox(ctx, sessionID string, info *types.SandboxInfo) error`\n  - [ ] Implement `DeleteSandboxBySessionID(ctx, sessionID string) error`\n  - [ ] Implement `ListInactiveSandboxes(ctx, since time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n  - [ ] Implement `ListExpiredSandboxes(ctx, threshold time.Time, limit int) ([]*types.SandboxInfo, error)`\n- [ ] Create unit tests for Store interface methods in `pkg/store/store_test.go`\n  - [ ] Test StoreSandbox and GetSandbox\n  - [ ] Test UpdateSandbox\n  - [ ] Test DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n  - [ ] Test ListInactiveSandboxes with valid time threshold\n  - [ ] Test ListExpiredSandboxes with valid threshold\n  - [ ] Test error handling for non-existent sessions\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/store -run TestStore` to verify Store interface tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 3: Implement Kubernetes client wrapper for deletion operations\n- [ ] Extend `pkg/workloadmanager/client/k8s_client.go` Client interface (if not already extended)\n  - [ ] Implement `DeleteSandbox(ctx, namespace, name string) error`\n  - [ ] Ensure GetAgentRuntime method exists\n  - [ ] Ensure GetCodeInterpreter method exists\n  - [ ] Ensure CreateSandbox method exists\n- [ ] Implement DeleteSandbox method\n  - [ ] Determine GVR based on resource type (Sandbox or SandboxClaim)\n  - [ ] Use dynamic client to delete resource\n  - [ ] Handle NotFound errors gracefully (return nil, not error)\n  - [ ] Return error for other deletion failures\n- [ ] Create or extend unit tests in `pkg/workloadmanager/client/k8s_client_test.go`\n  - [ ] Test DeleteSandbox for Sandbox resource\n  - [ ] Test DeleteSandbox for SandboxClaim resource\n  - [ ] Test DeleteSandbox with NotFound error (should succeed)\n  - [ ] Test DeleteSandbox with other errors (should fail)\n  - [ ] Test GetAgentRuntime and GetCodeInterpreter (if not tested)\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/client -run TestK8sClient` to verify K8sClient tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 4: Implement SandboxController deletion methods\n- [ ] Create or extend `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/sandbox.go`\n- [ ] Define SandboxController struct (if not exists)\n  - [ ] `k8sClient client.Client` - Kubernetes client\n  - [ ] `store store.Store` - Session store\n- [ ] Implement `DeleteSession(ctx, sessionID string) (*api.DeleteSessionResponse, error)`\n  - [ ] Retrieve sandbox metadata from store via store.GetSandbox\n  - [ ] Return error if not found\n  - [ ] Delete sandbox resource from Kubernetes via k8sClient.DeleteSandbox\n  - [ ] Handle NotFound error gracefully (continue to store deletion)\n  - [ ] Delete session record from store via store.DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n  - [ ] Return DeleteSessionResponse with sessionID and deletedAt\n- [ ] Implement `GetSession(ctx, sessionID string) (*api.GetSessionResponse, error)` (if not exists)\n  - [ ] Retrieve sandbox metadata from store\n  - [ ] Return error if not found\n  - [ ] Convert SandboxInfo to GetSessionResponse\n  - [ ] Return response\n- [ ] Create or extend unit tests in `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/sandbox_test.go`\n  - [ ] Test DeleteSession with valid session (deletes both K8s resource and store record)\n  - [ ] Test DeleteSession with non-existent session (returns error)\n  - [ ] Test DeleteSession with sandbox already deleted in K8s (succeeds, deletes store record)\n  - [ ] Test DeleteSession with store deletion failure (returns error)\n  - [ ] Test GetSession with valid session\n  - [ ] Test GetSession with non-existent session\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/controller -run TestSandboxController` to verify tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 5: Implement API types for deletion operations\n- [ ] Create or extend `pkg/workloadmanager/api/types.go`\n- [ ] Define DeleteSessionResponse struct\n  - [ ] `SessionID string`\n  - [ ] `DeletedAt time.Time`\n- [ ] Define DeleteSandboxResponse struct (if different from DeleteSessionResponse)\n  - [ ] `Message string`\n- [ ] Define error response types\n  - [ ] `ErrorResponse` struct with Code and Message fields\n- [ ] Define error code constants\n  - [ ] `ErrCodeBadRequest = \"BAD_REQUEST\"`\n  - [ ] `ErrCodeSessionNotFound = \"SESSION_NOT_FOUND\"`\n  - [ ] `ErrCodeInternalServerError = \"INTERNAL_SERVER_ERROR\"`\n- [ ] Create unit tests in `pkg/workloadmanager/api/types_test.go`\n  - [ ] Test DeleteSessionResponse serialization\n  - [ ] Test ErrorResponse serialization\n  - [ ] Test error code constants\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/api -run TestTypes` to verify tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 6: Implement HTTP Handler for manual deletion\n- [ ] Create or extend `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox.go`\n- [ ] Define SandboxHandler struct (if not exists)\n  - [ ] `dynamicClient dynamic.Interface`\n  - [ ] `storeClient store.Store`\n- [ ] Implement `HandleDeleteSandbox(c *gin.Context)`\n  - [ ] Extract sessionId from path parameter\n  - [ ] Validate sessionId is not empty (return 400 if empty)\n  - [ ] Retrieve sandbox info from store via storeClient.GetSandbox\n  - [ ] Return 404 if not found\n  - [ ] Determine GVR based on sandbox.Kind (Sandbox or SandboxClaim)\n  - [ ] Create context with timeout (DeleteTimeout)\n  - [ ] Delete sandbox resource via dynamicClient\n  - [ ] Handle NotFound error gracefully (continue to store deletion)\n  - [ ] Return 500 on other errors\n  - [ ] Delete session from store via storeClient.DeleteSandboxBySessionID\n  - [ ] Log warning on store deletion failure\n  - [ ] Return 200 OK with DeleteSandboxResponse\n- [ ] Implement error response helper functions\n  - [ ] `Error(c *gin.Context, statusCode int, code string, message string)`\n  - [ ] `JSON(c *gin.Context, statusCode int, data interface{})`\n- [ ] Create unit tests in `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/sandbox_test.go`\n  - [ ] Test HandleDeleteSandbox with valid session\n  - [ ] Test HandleDeleteSandbox with missing sessionId\n  - [ ] Test HandleDeleteSandbox with non-existent session\n  - [ ] Test HandleDeleteSandbox with sandbox already deleted in K8s\n  - [ ] Test HandleDeleteSandbox with K8s deletion error\n  - [ ] Test error response formatting\n  - [ ] Test JSON response formatting\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handler -run TestHandleDeleteSandbox` to verify tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 7: Register DELETE route in HTTP router\n- [ ] Create or extend `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/routes.go`\n- [ ] Implement route registration function\n  - [ ] Register `DELETE /v1/sessions/:sessionId` -> handler.HandleDeleteSandbox\n- [ ] Apply middleware to the route\n  - [ ] CORS middleware\n  - [ ] Request ID middleware\n  - [ ] Logging middleware\n  - [ ] Recovery middleware\n  - [ ] Authentication middleware (if enabled)\n- [ ] Create unit tests in `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/routes_test.go`\n  - [ ] Verify DELETE route is registered\n  - [ ] Verify route handler is correct\n  - [ ] Test middleware is applied\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/handler -run TestRoutes` to verify tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 8: Implement GarbageCollector structure and lifecycle\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n- [ ] Define GarbageCollector struct\n  - [ ] `dynamicClient dynamic.Interface`\n  - [ ] `storeClient store.Store`\n  - [ ] `interval time.Duration`\n  - [ ] `ctx context.Context`\n  - [ ] `cancel context.CancelFunc`\n- [ ] Implement `NewGarbageCollector(dynamicClient dynamic.Interface, storeClient store.Store, interval time.Duration) *GarbageCollector`\n  - [ ] Initialize collector with dependencies\n  - [ ] Create context with cancel function\n  - [ ] Return collector instance\n- [ ] Implement `Start()` method\n  - [ ] Launch goroutine running gcLoop()\n  - [ ] Log start message\n- [ ] Implement `Stop()` method\n  - [ ] Call cancel() to stop gcLoop\n  - [ ] Log stop message\n- [ ] Implement `gcLoop()` method\n  - [ ] Create ticker with interval\n  - [ ] Defer ticker.Stop()\n  - [ ] Loop forever\n  - [ ] Select on ctx.Done() or ticker.C\n  - [ ] Call tick() on each tick\n  - [ ] Return on ctx.Done()\n- [ ] Create unit tests in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n  - [ ] Test NewGarbageCollector initialization\n  - [ ] Test Start() launches goroutine\n  - [ ] Test Stop() cancels context\n  - [ ] Test gcLoop() respects context cancellation\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollectorLifecycle` to verify tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 9: Implement GarbageCollector tick() method\n- [ ] Implement `tick()` method in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n  - [ ] Create context with timeout (GCSingleTickTimeout)\n  - [ ] Defer cancel()\n  - [ ] Calculate idleThreshold (now - DefaultSandboxIdleTimeout)\n  - [ ] Calculate expiredThreshold (now)\n  - [ ] List inactive sandboxes via storeClient.ListInactiveSandboxes\n  - [ ] Log error if list fails\n  - [ ] For each inactive sandbox, call deleteSandbox with CleanupReasonIdleTimeout\n  - [ ] List expired sandboxes via storeClient.ListExpiredSandboxes\n  - [ ] Log error if list fails\n  - [ ] For each expired sandbox, call deleteSandbox with CleanupReasonExpired\n- [ ] Create unit tests in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n  - [ ] Test tick() with idle sandboxes\n  - [ ] Test tick() with expired sandboxes\n  - [ ] Test tick() with both idle and expired sandboxes\n  - [ ] Test tick() with store list errors\n  - [ ] Test tick() respects timeout\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollectorTick` to verify tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 10: Implement GarbageCollector deleteSandbox() method\n- [ ] Implement `deleteSandbox(ctx, sandbox *types.SandboxInfo, reason wmTypes.SandboxCleanupReason)` in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n  - [ ] Create CleanupAuditEntry with sessionID, sandboxID, namespace, reason, deletedAt\n  - [ ] Determine GVR based on sandbox.Kind\n  - [ ] Create context with timeout (DeleteTimeout)\n  - [ ] Defer cancel()\n  - [ ] Delete sandbox resource via dynamicClient\n  - [ ] Handle NotFound error (set success=true, continue to store deletion)\n  - [ ] Handle other errors (set success=false, set ErrorMessage, log error)\n  - [ ] Delete session from store via storeClient.DeleteSandboxBySessionID (if K8s deletion succeeded or not found)\n  - [ ] Log warning on store deletion failure\n  - [ ] Call recordAudit() with auditEntry\n  - [ ] Log success message if deletion succeeded\n- [ ] Create unit tests in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n  - [ ] Test deleteSandbox with successful K8s deletion\n  - [ ] Test deleteSandbox with NotFound error (should succeed)\n  - [ ] Test deleteSandbox with other K8s errors\n  - [ ] Test deleteSandbox with Sandbox resource type\n  - [ ] Test deleteSandbox with SandboxClaim resource type\n  - [ ] Test deleteSandbox with store deletion failure\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollectorDeleteSandbox` to verify tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 11: Implement GarbageCollector recordAudit() method\n- [ ] Implement `recordAudit(auditEntry *wmTypes.CleanupAuditEntry)` in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.go`\n  - [ ] Log structured audit entry using klog\n  - [ ] Include all audit fields: sessionID, sandboxID, namespace, reason, deletedAt, success, errorMessage\n  - [ ] Use appropriate log level (Info for success, Warning/Error for failure)\n- [ ] Create unit tests in `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector_test.go`\n  - [ ] Test recordAudit() with successful cleanup\n  - [ ] Test recordAudit() with failed cleanup\n  - [ ] Verify log output format\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollectorRecordAudit` to verify tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 12: Integrate GarbageCollector into WorkloadManager server\n- [ ] Create or extend `pkg/workloadmanager/server/server.go`\n- [ ] Add GarbageCollector field to Server struct\n- [ ] Modify server initialization to create GarbageCollector instance\n  - [ ] Pass dynamic client and store client\n  - [ ] Use GCInterval from configuration\n- [ ] Start GarbageCollector in server startup\n  - [ ] Call gc.Start() after other components are initialized\n- [ ] Stop GarbageCollector in server shutdown\n  - [ ] Call gc.Stop() in graceful shutdown handler\n  - [ ] Wait for gc goroutine to exit\n- [ ] Update server configuration to support GC interval\n  - [ ] Add GCInterval to Config struct\n  - [ ] Default to GCInterval constant if not specified\n- [ ] Create integration tests\n  - [ ] Test server starts and stops GarbageCollector\n  - [ ] Test GarbageCollector runs periodic cleanup\n  - [ ] Test server shutdown stops GarbageCollector gracefully\n\n**Verification**: Run integration tests to verify GarbageCollector is properly integrated\n\n---\n\n### Task 13: Implement session expiration and idle timeout tracking\n- [ ] Ensure SandboxInfo struct includes expiration fields\n  - [ ] `CreatedAt time.Time`\n  - [ ] `ExpiresAt time.Time`\n  - [ ] `LastActivityAt time.Time`\n- [ ] Implement session creation logic (if not exists in AR-005)\n  - [ ] Set CreatedAt to current time\n  - [ ] Set ExpiresAt to CreatedAt + DefaultSandboxTTL\n  - [ ] Set LastActivityAt to current time\n- [ ] Implement session update logic\n  - [ ] Update LastActivityAt on activity (optional, can be handled elsewhere)\n- [ ] Verify Store.ListInactiveSandboxes implementation\n  - [ ] Query for sessions with LastActivityAt < threshold\n  - [ ] Return list of sessions\n- [ ] Verify Store.ListExpiredSandboxes implementation\n  - [ ] Query for sessions with ExpiresAt <= threshold\n  - [ ] Return list of sessions\n- [ ] Create unit tests\n  - [ ] Test session expiration calculation\n  - [ ] Test session idle timeout detection\n  - [ ] Test ListInactiveSandboxes with various time thresholds\n  - [ ] Test ListExpiredSandboxes with various thresholds\n\n**Verification**: Run unit tests to verify session expiration and idle timeout tracking works correctly\n\n---\n\n### Task 14: Implement comprehensive integration tests for deletion flow\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n- [ ] Implement `TestDeleteSessionEndToEnd`\n  - [ ] Setup test Kubernetes client (fake)\n  - [ ] Setup test Store (in-memory Redis)\n  - [ ] Create test sandbox session in Store\n  - [ ] Create test Sandbox CR in Kubernetes\n  - [ ] Call DeleteSession API\n  - [ ] Verify Sandbox CR is deleted from Kubernetes\n  - [ ] Verify session is deleted from Store\n  - [ ] Verify response is correct\n  - [ ] Test idempotency (call DeleteSession twice, second should succeed)\n- [ ] Implement `TestDeleteSessionNotFound`\n  - [ ] Call DeleteSession with non-existent session\n  - [ ] Verify 404 error is returned\n- [ ] Implement `TestDeleteSessionK8sNotFound`\n  - [ ] Create session in Store but not in Kubernetes\n  - [ ] Call DeleteSession\n  - [ ] Verify store record is deleted\n  - [ ] Verify operation succeeds\n- [ ] Implement `TestConcurrentDeletion`\n  - [ ] Create test sandbox session\n  - [ ] Launch multiple concurrent DeleteSession calls\n  - [ ] Verify all calls succeed (eventual consistency)\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestDeleteSessionIntegration` to verify integration tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 15: Implement comprehensive integration tests for garbage collection\n- [ ] Extend `pkg/workloadmanager/integration_test.go`\n- [ ] Implement `TestGarbageCollectorIdleCleanup`\n  - [ ] Setup test Kubernetes client and Store\n  - [ ] Create test sandbox sessions with old LastActivityAt\n  - [ ] Create GarbageCollector with short interval\n  - [ ] Start GarbageCollector\n  - [ ] Wait for at least one GC cycle\n  - [ ] Stop GarbageCollector\n  - [ ] Verify idle sandboxes are deleted from Kubernetes\n  - [ ] Verify idle sandboxes are deleted from Store\n  - [ ] Verify cleanup reason is idle_timeout\n- [ ] Implement `TestGarbageCollectorExpiredCleanup`\n  - [ ] Similar to idle cleanup test\n  - [ ] Create sessions with old ExpiresAt\n  - [ ] Verify cleanup reason is expired\n- [ ] Implement `TestGarbageCollectorMixedCleanup`\n  - [ ] Create mix of idle, expired, and active sessions\n  - [ ] Verify only idle and expired are cleaned up\n  - [ ] Verify active sessions remain\n- [ ] Implement `TestGarbageCollectorFailureHandling`\n  - [ ] Setup store with sessions that don't exist in Kubernetes\n  - [ ] Verify cleanup handles NotFound errors gracefully\n  - [ ] Verify other sessions are still cleaned up\n\n**Verification**: Run `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager -run TestGarbageCollectorIntegration` to verify integration tests pass\n\n---\n\n### Task 16: Implement metrics and observability\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/metrics/metrics.go` (if not exists)\n- [ ] Define Prometheus metrics for garbage collection\n  - [ ] `metricGCDeletedTotal` - CounterVec with reason label\n  - [ ] `metricGCFailedTotal` - CounterVec with reason label\n  - [ ] `metricGCDurationSeconds` - Histogram for tick duration\n  - [ ] `metricActiveSandboxes` - Gauge for active sandbox count\n  - [ ] `metricExpiredSandboxes` - Gauge for expired sandbox count\n  - [ ] `metricInactiveSandboxes` - Gauge for inactive sandbox count\n- [ ] Implement metric registration in init()\n- [ ] Update GarbageCollector to emit metrics\n  - [ ] Increment gcDeleted on successful deletion\n  - [ ] Increment gcFailed on failed deletion\n  - [ ] Record tick duration\n  - [ ] Update gauge metrics for sandbox counts\n- [ ] Create unit tests\n  - [ ] Test metrics are registered\n  - [ ] Test metrics are incremented correctly\n  - [ ] Test histogram records duration\n- [ ] Add logging for deletion operations\n  - [ ] Log successful deletions with session details\n  - [ ] Log failed deletions with error details\n  - [ ] Use structured logging with klog\n\n**Verification**: Run tests and verify metrics are emitted correctly\n\n---\n\n### Task 17: Implement error handling and idempotency\n- [ ] Review all deletion operations for idempotency\n  - [ ] Ensure DeleteSession can be called multiple times safely\n  - [ ] Ensure GarbageCollector handles already-deleted resources\n- [ ] Add error handling edge cases\n  - [ ] K8s API timeout (context deadline exceeded)\n  - [ ] Store connection errors\n  - [ ] Concurrent deletion (race conditions)\n  - [ ] Partial failures (K8s deleted, store not deleted)\n- [ ] Add retry logic (optional, for GarbageCollector)\n  - [ ] Failed deletions are retried on next GC cycle\n  - [ ] Exponential backoff for transient errors\n- [ ] Create unit tests for error scenarios\n  - [ ] Test K8s timeout\n  - [ ] Test store connection errors\n  - [ ] Test concurrent deletion\n  - [ ] Test partial failures\n\n**Verification**: Run tests to verify error handling and idempotency\n\n---\n\n### Task 18: Update RBAC permissions and security\n- [ ] Update Kubernetes RBAC manifests\n  - [ ] Add delete permission for agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxes\n  - [ ] Add delete permission for extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/sandboxclaims\n  - [ ] Add list permission for pods (for verification)\n- [ ] Update ClusterRole or Role in deployment manifests\n- [ ] Verify WorkloadManager service account has correct permissions\n- [ ] Implement authorization checks in handler (optional)\n  - [ ] Verify user has permission to delete in sandbox's namespace\n  - [ ] Use Kubernetes SubjectAccessReview API\n- [ ] Create security tests\n  - [ ] Test deletion with insufficient permissions\n  - [ ] Test deletion with proper permissions\n  - [ ] Test cross-namespace deletion (should fail)\n\n**Verification**: Run security tests to verify RBAC permissions are correct\n\n---\n\n### Task 19: Create comprehensive documentation\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/README.md` (if not exists or update)\n  - [ ] Overview of WorkloadManager package\n  - [ ] Architecture diagram\n  - [ ] GarbageCollector documentation\n  - [ ] Sandbox lifecycle documentation\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/controller/README.md`\n  - [ ] SandboxController documentation\n  - [ ] DeleteSession API documentation\n  - [ ] Usage examples\n- [ ] Create `pkg/workloadmanager/handler/README.md`\n  - [ ] HTTP handler documentation\n  - [ ] DELETE endpoint documentation\n  - [ ] Request/response examples\n- [ Create `pkg/workloadmanager/garbage_collector.md` (or include in main README)\n  - [ ] GarbageCollector design overview\n  - [ ] Configuration options\n  - [ ] Cleanup strategies\n- [ ] Update API documentation\n  - [ ] Document DELETE /v1/sessions/:sessionId endpoint\n  - [ ] Include request/response examples\n  - [ ] Document error codes\n- [ ] Update configuration documentation\n  - [ ] Document GCInterval configuration\n  - [ ] Document timeout configurations\n  - [ ] Document label and annotation constants\n\n**Verification**: Review documentation for completeness and accuracy\n\n---\n\n### Task 20: Final verification and cleanup\n- [ ] Run full test suite: `go test ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n  - [ ] Verify all unit tests pass\n  - [ ] Verify all integration tests pass\n- [ ] Run static analysis: `go vet ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n  - [ ] Fix any warnings or errors\n- [ ] Run linter if configured (e.g., golangci-lint)\n  - [ ] Fix any linting issues\n- [ ] Run gofmt: `gofmt -s -w ./pkg/workloadmanager/`\n  - [ ] Ensure code is properly formatted\n- [ ] Update go.mod: `go mod tidy`\n  - [ ] Remove unused dependencies\n  - [ ] Update go.sum\n- [ ] Build package: `go build ./pkg/workloadmanager/...`\n  - [ ] Verify all packages build successfully\n- [ ] Test end-to-end workflow\n  - [ ] Create sandbox via AR-005\n  - [ ] Wait for expiration\n  - [ ] Verify GarbageCollector cleans up\n  - [ ] Test manual deletion\n  - [ ] Verify resources are properly cleaned\n- [ ] Create CHANGELOG entry for AR-006\n- [ ] Update main project README with AR-006 information\n- [ ] Tag release if applicable\n\n**Verification**: All tests pass, code is linted, packages build successfully, end-to-end workflow works\n\n---\n\n## Summary\n\n**Total Tasks**: 20\n**Estimated Effort**: M (Medium) - 10-15 hours\n\n### Key Deliverables\n1. **GarbageCollector** - Automatic cleanup of idle and expired sandboxes\n2. **SandboxController.DeleteSession** - Manual deletion API\n3. **HTTP Handler** - DELETE /v1/sessions/:sessionId endpoint\n4. **Store Extensions** - ListInactiveSandboxes, ListExpiredSandboxes methods\n5. **K8sClient Deletion** - DeleteSandbox method\n6. **API Types** - DeleteSessionResponse, error types\n7. **Metrics** - Prometheus metrics for cleanup operations\n8. **Documentation** - Comprehensive API and design documentation\n9. **RBAC Updates** - Permissions for deletion operations\n10. **Tests** - Unit and integration tests\n\n### Success Criteria\n- All unit tests pass with >80% code coverage\n- All integration tests pass\n- Manual deletion works correctly via API\n- GarbageCollector cleans up idle sandboxes\n- GarbageCollector cleans up expired sandboxes\n- Resources are properly cleaned up (K8s + Store)\n- Error handling returns appropriate HTTP status codes\n- Operations are idempotent\n- Metrics are emitted correctly\n- Logs are structured and informative\n- RBAC permissions are correct\n- Code passes static analysis and linting\n- Documentation is complete and accurate\n\n### Dependencies\n- Go 1.24+\n- Kubernetes cluster (for testing)\n- Redis/Valkey (for session store)\n- agent-sandbox CRD (agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1)\n- SandboxClaim CRD (extensions.agents.x-k8s.io/v1alpha1)\n- AR-005 (Sandbox creation) - for complete lifecycle testing\n- k8s.io/client-go v0.34.1\n- k8s.io/api v0.34.1\n- k8s.io/apimachinery v0.34.1\n- go-redis/v9 or valkey-go (Redis client)\n- gin-gonic/gin (HTTP framework)\n- prometheus/client_golang (metrics)\n\n### Blocked By\n- None (design stage ST-3 completed)\n\n### Blocks\n- None (this is a lifecycle enhancement, can proceed independently)\n\n### Notes\n- AR-006 complements AR-005 (sandbox creation) to provide complete lifecycle management\n- GarbageCollector runs independently in background, can be started/stopped with server\n- Manual deletion and automatic cleanup are independent features\n- Idempotency ensures safe retries and concurrent operations\n- Error handling is designed to be resilient to transient failures","filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-glm-4.7_20260410T163120Z/changes/AR-006/tasks.md","time":{"start":1775845214287,"end":1775845214312}}}}
